198 template <class T>
199 class Local {
200  public:
201  V8_INLINE Local() : val_(nullptr) {}
202  template <class S>
203  V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
204  : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
210  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
211  }
212 
216  V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
217 
221  V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = nullptr; }
222 
223  V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
224 
225  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
226 
237  template <class S>
238  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
239  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
240  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
241  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
242  if (b == nullptr) return false;
243  return *a == *b;
244  }
245 
246  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
247  const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
248  internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
249  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
250  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
251  if (b == nullptr) return false;
252  return *a == *b;
253  }
254 
265  template <class S>
266  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
267  return !operator==(that);
268  }
269 
270  template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
271  const Persistent<S>& that) const {
272  return !operator==(that);
273  }
274 
280  template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
281 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
282  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
283  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
284  if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
285 #endif
286  return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
287  }
288 
294  template <class S>
295  V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
296  return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
297  }
298 
304  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
305  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
306  const PersistentBase<T>& that);
307  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
308  const BasicTracedReference<T>& that);
309 
310  private:
311  friend class TracedReferenceBase;
312  friend class Utils;
313  template<class F> friend class Eternal;
314  template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
315  template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
316  template<class F> friend class Local;
317  template <class F>
318  friend class MaybeLocal;
319  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
320  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
321  friend class String;
322  friend class Object;
323  friend class Context;
324  friend class Isolate;
325  friend class Private;
326  template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
327  friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
328  friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
329  friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
330  friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
331  friend class HandleScope;
332  friend class EscapableHandleScope;
333  template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
334  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
335  template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
336  template <class F>
337  friend class ReturnValue;
338  template <class F>
339  friend class Traced;
340  template <class F>
341  friend class TracedGlobal;
342  template <class F>
343  friend class BasicTracedReference;
344  template <class F>
345  friend class TracedReference;

347  explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
348  V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
349  T* val_;

386  template <class S>

415 template <class T> class Eternal {

432 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
433 static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
434 
435 template <typename T>
436 class WeakCallbackInfo {
437  public:
438  using Callback = void (*)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
439 
440  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
441  void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
442  Callback* callback)
443  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
444  for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
445  embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
446  }
447  }
448 
449  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
450  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
451  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
452 
453  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
454  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
455  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
456  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
457  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
458  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
459  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
460 
461  private:
462  Isolate* isolate_;
463  T* parameter_;
464  Callback* callback_;
465  void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
466 };
467 
468 
469 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
470 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
471 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
472 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
473 // possible to request a second pass callback.
474 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
475

514  return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this);
515  }

521  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;

529  internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
530  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
531  if (b == nullptr) return false;
532  return *a == *b;
533  }

630 class NonCopyablePersistentTraits {

632  using NonCopyablePersistent = Persistent<T, NonCopyablePersistentTraits<T>>;
633  static const bool kResetInDestructor = false;
634  template<class S, class M>
635  V8_INLINE static void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
636  NonCopyablePersistent* dest) {
637  static_assert(sizeof(S) < 0,
638  "NonCopyablePersistentTraits::Copy is not instantiable");
639  }
640 };

667 template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
668  public:
672  V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
678  template <class S>
679  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
680  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
681  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
682  }
688  template <class S, class M2>
689  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
690  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
691  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
692  }
699  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {
700  Copy(that);
701  }
702  template <class S, class M2>
703  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
704  Copy(that);
705  }
706  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) {
707  Copy(that);
708  return *this;
709  }
710  template <class S, class M2>
711  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
712  Copy(that);
713  return *this;
714  }
720  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
721  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
722  }
723 
724  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
725  template <class S>
726  V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
727 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
728  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
729  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
730  if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
731 #endif
732  return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
733  }
734 
735  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
736  template <class S>
737  V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
738  return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
739  }
740 
741  private:
742  friend class Isolate;
743  friend class Utils;
744  template<class F> friend class Local;
745  template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
746  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
747 
748  explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
749  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
750  template<class S, class M2>
751  V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
752 };

833 class TracedReferenceBase {
834  public:
839  bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
840 
845  V8_INLINE void Reset();
846 
850  V8_INLINE v8::Local<v8::Value> Get(v8::Isolate* isolate) const;
851 
856  bool IsEmptyThreadSafe() const {
857  return this->GetSlotThreadSafe() == nullptr;
858  }
859 
863  V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
864 
869  V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
870 
871  protected:
875  void SetSlotThreadSafe(void* new_val) {
876  reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<void*>*>(&val_)->store(
877  new_val, std::memory_order_relaxed);
878  }
879 
883  const void* GetSlotThreadSafe() const {
884  return reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<const void*> const*>(&val_)->load(
885  std::memory_order_relaxed);
886  }
887 
888  // val_ points to a GlobalHandles node.
889  internal::Address* val_ = nullptr;
890 
891  friend class internal::BasicTracedReferenceExtractor;
892  template <typename F>
893  friend class Local;
894  template <typename U>
895  friend bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase&, const Local<U>&);
896  friend bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase&,
897  const TracedReferenceBase&);
898 };

926  const_cast<BasicTracedReference<T>&>(*this));

930  T* operator*() const { return reinterpret_cast<T*>(val_); }

939 
940  V8_INLINE static internal::Address* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that, void* slot,
941  DestructionMode destruction_mode);

961 template <typename T>

985  BasicTracedReference<T>::kWithDestructor);

1059  V8_INLINE TracedGlobal<S>& As() const {
1060  return reinterpret_cast<TracedGlobal<S>&>(
1061  const_cast<TracedGlobal<T>&>(*this));
1062  }

1075  void* parameter, WeakCallbackInfo<void>::Callback callback);
1076 };

1089 template <typename T>
1090 class TracedReference : public BasicTracedReference<T> {
1091  public:
1092  using BasicTracedReference<T>::Reset;
1093 
1097  TracedReference() : BasicTracedReference<T>() {}
1098 
1105  template <class S>
1106  TracedReference(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that) : BasicTracedReference<T>() {
1107  this->val_ = this->New(isolate, that.val_, &this->val_,
1108  BasicTracedReference<T>::kWithoutDestructor);
1109  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
1110  }
1111 
1116  V8_INLINE TracedReference(TracedReference&& other) {
1117  // Forward to operator=.
1118  *this = std::move(other);
1119  }
1120 
1125  template <typename S>
1126  V8_INLINE TracedReference(TracedReference<S>&& other) {
1127  // Forward to operator=.
1128  *this = std::move(other);
1129  }
1130 
1135  V8_INLINE TracedReference(const TracedReference& other) {
1136  // Forward to operator=;
1137  *this = other;
1138  }
1139 
1144  template <typename S>
1145  V8_INLINE TracedReference(const TracedReference<S>& other) {
1146  // Forward to operator=;
1147  *this = other;
1148  }
1149 
1153  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(TracedReference&& rhs);
1154 
1158  template <class S>
1159  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(TracedReference<S>&& rhs);
1160 
1164  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference& rhs);
1165 
1169  template <class S>
1170  V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference<S>& rhs);
1171 
1176  template <class S>
1177  V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
1178 
1179  template <class S>
1180  V8_INLINE TracedReference<S>& As() const {
1181  return reinterpret_cast<TracedReference<S>&>(
1182  const_cast<TracedReference<T>&>(*this));
1183  }

1394 class ScriptOriginOptions {
1395  public:
1396  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1397  bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1398  bool is_module = false)
1399  : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1400  (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1401  (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1402  V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1403  : flags_(flags &
1404  (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1405 
1406  bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1407  return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1408  }
1409  bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1410  bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1411  bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1412 
1413  int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1414 
1415  private:
1416  enum {
1417  kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1418  kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1419  kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1420  kIsModule = 1 << 3
1421  };
1422  const int flags_;
1423 };

1800 class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1801  public:
1809  struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1810  enum BufferPolicy {
1811  BufferNotOwned,
1812  BufferOwned
1813  };
1814 
1815  CachedData()
1816  : data(nullptr),
1817  length(0),
1818  rejected(false),
1819  buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1820 
1821  // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1822  // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1823  // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1824  // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1825  CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1826  BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1827  ~CachedData();
1828  // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1829  // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1830  const uint8_t* data;
1831  int length;
1832  bool rejected;
1833  BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1834 
1835  // Prevent copying.
1836  CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1837  CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1838  };
1839 
1843  class Source {
1844  public:
1845  // Source takes ownership of CachedData.
1846  V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
1847  CachedData* cached_data = nullptr);
1848  V8_INLINE explicit Source(Local<String> source_string,
1849  CachedData* cached_data = nullptr);
1850  V8_INLINE ~Source();
1851 
1852  // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1853  // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1854  // alive.
1855  V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1856 
1857  V8_INLINE const ScriptOriginOptions& GetResourceOptions() const;
1858 
1859  // Prevent copying.
1860  Source(const Source&) = delete;
1861  Source& operator=(const Source&) = delete;
1862 
1863  private:
1864  friend class ScriptCompiler;
1865 
1866  Local<String> source_string;
1867 
1868  // Origin information

1878  // set when calling a compile method.

3877  // Implements CreateDataProperty (ECMA-262, 7.3.4).
3878  //
3879  // Defines a configurable, writable, enumerable property with the given value
3880  // on the object unless the property already exists and is not configurable
3881  // or the object is not extensible.
3882  //
3883  // Returns true on success.

3885  Local<Name> key,

3901  // Implements Object.DefineProperty(O, P, Attributes), see Ecma-262 19.1.2.4.
3902  //
3903  // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3904  // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3905  //
3906  // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
3907  //
3908  // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
3909  // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.
3910  //
3911  // The PropertyDescriptor can change when redefining a property.
3912  //
3913  // Returns true on success.

4422 template<typename T>
4423 class ReturnValue {
4424  public:
4425  template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
4426  : value_(that.value_) {
4427  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
4428  }
4429  // Local setters
4430  template <typename S>
4431  V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
4432  template <typename S>
4433  V8_INLINE void Set(const BasicTracedReference<S>& handle);
4434  template <typename S>
4435  V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
4436  // Fast primitive setters
4437  V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
4438  V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
4439  V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
4440  V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
4441  // Fast JS primitive setters
4442  V8_INLINE void SetNull();
4443  V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
4444  V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
4445  // Convenience getter for Isolate
4446  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
4447 
4448  // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
4449  template <typename S>
4450  V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
4451 
4452  // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
4453  // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
4454  // value.
4455  V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
4456 
4457  private:
4458  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
4459  template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
4460  template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
4461  template <class F, class G, class H>
4462  friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
4463  V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Address value) { *value_ = value; }
4464  V8_INLINE internal::Address GetDefaultValue();
4465  V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Address* slot);
4466  internal::Address* value_;
4467 };

7204 class V8_EXPORT Extension { // NOLINT
7205  public:
7206  // Note that the strings passed into this constructor must live as long
7207  // as the Extension itself.
7208  Extension(const char* name, const char* source = nullptr, int dep_count = 0,
7209  const char** deps = nullptr, int source_length = -1);
7210  virtual ~Extension() { delete source_; }
7211  virtual Local<FunctionTemplate> GetNativeFunctionTemplate(
7212  Isolate* isolate, Local<String> name) {
7213  return Local<FunctionTemplate>();
7214  }
7215 
7216  const char* name() const { return name_; }
7217  size_t source_length() const { return source_length_; }
7218  const String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* source() const {
7219  return source_;
7220  }
7221  int dependency_count() const { return dep_count_; }
7222  const char** dependencies() const { return deps_; }
7223  void set_auto_enable(bool value) { auto_enable_ = value; }
7224  bool auto_enable() { return auto_enable_; }
7225 
7226  // Disallow copying and assigning.
7227  Extension(const Extension&) = delete;
7228  void operator=(const Extension&) = delete;
7229 
7230  private:
7231  const char* name_;
7232  size_t source_length_; // expected to initialize before source_
7233  String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* source_;
7234  int dep_count_;
7235  const char** deps_;
7236  bool auto_enable_;
7237 };

7940 
7946 struct JitCodeEvent {
7947  enum EventType {
7948  CODE_ADDED,
7949  CODE_MOVED,
7950  CODE_REMOVED,
7951  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
7952  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
7953  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
7954  };
7955  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
7956  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
7957  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
7958  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
7959  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
7960  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
7961 
7962  // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
7963  // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
7964  // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
7965  // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
7966  // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
7967  // function.
7968  enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
7969 
7970  // Type of event.
7971  EventType type;
7972  CodeType code_type;
7973  // Start of the instructions.
7974  void* code_start;
7975  // Size of the instructions.
7976  size_t code_len;
7977  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
7978  Local<UnboundScript> script;
7979  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
7980  // code line information which is returned from the
7981  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
7982  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
7983  void* user_data;
7984 
7985  struct name_t {
7986  // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
7987  // zero-terminated.
7988  const char* str;
7989  // Number of chars in str.
7990  size_t len;
7991  };
7992 
7993  struct line_info_t {
7994  // PC offset
7995  size_t offset;
7996  // Code position
7997  size_t pos;
7998  // The position type.
7999  PositionType position_type;
8000  };
8001 
8002  struct wasm_source_info_t {
8003  // Source file name.
8004  const char* filename;
8005  // Length of filename.
8006  size_t filename_size;
8007  // Line number table, which maps offsets of JITted code to line numbers of
8008  // source file.
8009  const line_info_t* line_number_table;
8010  // Number of entries in the line number table.
8011  size_t line_number_table_size;
8012  };
8013 
8014  wasm_source_info_t* wasm_source_info;
8015 
8016  union {
8017  // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
8018  struct name_t name;
8019 
8020  // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
8021  struct line_info_t line_info;
8022 
8023  // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
8024  void* new_code_start;
8025  };
8026 
8027  Isolate* isolate;
8028 };
8029 
8035 enum RAILMode : unsigned {
8036  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
8037  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
8038  // Throughput may be throttled.
8039  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
8040  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
8041  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
8042  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
8043  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
8044  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
8045  // in this mode.
8046  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
8047  // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
8048  // turn off latency optimizations.
8049  PERFORMANCE_LOAD
8050 };

10220 template <class T>
10221 class Maybe {
10222  public:
10223  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
10224  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
10225 
10229  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
10230 
10235  V8_INLINE void Check() const {
10236  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
10237  }
10238 
10243  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
10244  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
10245  return IsJust();
10246  }
10247 
10252  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
10253  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
10254  return value_;
10255  }
10256 
10261  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
10262  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
10263  }
10264 
10265  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
10266  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
10267  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
10268  }
10269 
10270  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
10271  return !operator==(other);
10272  }
10273 
10274  private:
10275  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
10276  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
10277 
10278  bool has_value_;
10279  T value_;
10280 
10281  template <class U>
10282  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
10283  template <class U>
10284  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
10285 };
10286 
10287 template <class T>
10288 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
10289  return Maybe<T>();
10290 }
10291 
10292 template <class T>
10293 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
10294  return Maybe<T>(t);
10295 }
10296 
10297 // A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
10298 template <>
10299 class Maybe<void> {
10300  public:
10301  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
10302  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
10303 
10304  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
10305  return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
10306  }
10307 
10308  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
10309  return !operator==(other);
10310  }
10311 
10312  private:
10313  struct JustTag {};
10314 
10315  Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
10316  explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
10317 
10318  bool is_valid_;
10319 
10320  template <class U>
10321  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
10322  friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
10323 };
10324 
10325 inline Maybe<void> JustVoid() { return Maybe<void>(Maybe<void>::JustTag()); }

10999 template <class T>
11000 Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
11001  if (that == nullptr) return Local<T>();
11002  T* that_ptr = that;
11003  internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that_ptr);
11004  return Local<T>(reinterpret_cast<T*>(HandleScope::CreateHandle(
11005  reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), *p)));
11006 }

11053 template <class T, class M>
11054 template <class S, class M2>
11055 void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
11056  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
11057  this->Reset();
11058  if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
11059  internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
11060  this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyGlobalReference(p));
11061  M::Copy(that, this);
11062 }

11068  return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_)) ==
11069  I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
11070 }

11077  val_ = nullptr;

11105  P* parameter, typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
11106  WeakCallbackType type) {
11107  using Callback = WeakCallbackInfo<void>::Callback;
11108 #if (__GNUC__ >= 8) && !defined(__clang__)
11109 #pragma GCC diagnostic push
11110 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wcast-function-type"
11111 #endif
11112  V8::MakeWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_), parameter,
11113  reinterpret_cast<Callback>(callback), type);
11114 #if (__GNUC__ >= 8) && !defined(__clang__)
11115 #pragma GCC diagnostic pop
11116 #endif
11117 }

11142  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + I::kNodeClassIdOffset;

11156 template <class T>
11157 Global<T>::Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) {
11158  if (other.val_ != nullptr) {
11159  V8::MoveGlobalReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&other.val_),
11160  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
11161  other.val_ = nullptr;
11162  }
11163 }
11164 
11165 template <class T>
11166 template <class S>
11167 Global<T>& Global<T>::operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) {
11168  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
11169  if (this != &rhs) {
11170  this->Reset();
11171  if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
11172  this->val_ = rhs.val_;
11173  V8::MoveGlobalReference(
11174  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&rhs.val_),
11175  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
11176  rhs.val_ = nullptr;
11177  }
11178  }
11179  return *this;
11180 }

11182 template <class T>
11183 internal::Address* BasicTracedReference<T>::New(
11184  Isolate* isolate, T* that, void* slot, DestructionMode destruction_mode) {
11185  if (that == nullptr) return nullptr;
11186  internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that);
11187  return V8::GlobalizeTracedReference(
11188  reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), p,
11189  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(slot),
11190  destruction_mode == kWithDestructor);
11191 }

11194  if (IsEmpty()) return;
11195  V8::DisposeTracedGlobal(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_));
11196  SetSlotThreadSafe(nullptr);
11197 }

11204 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase& lhs,
11205  const TracedReferenceBase& rhs) {
11206  v8::internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Address*>(lhs.val_);
11207  v8::internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Address*>(rhs.val_);
11208  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
11209  if (b == nullptr) return false;
11210  return *a == *b;
11211 }

11217  v8::internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Address*>(*rhs);
11218  if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;

11241 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const v8::Local<U>& lhs,
11242  const TracedReferenceBase& rhs) {
11243  return !(rhs == lhs);
11244 }

11250  Reset();
11251  if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
11252  this->val_ = this->New(isolate, other.val_, &this->val_,
11253  BasicTracedReference<T>::kWithDestructor);
11254 }

11275  V8::MoveTracedGlobalReference(
11276  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&rhs.val_),
11277  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
11278  }
11279  return *this;
11280 }

11282 template <class T>
11283 TracedGlobal<T>& TracedGlobal<T>::operator=(const TracedGlobal& rhs) {
11284  if (this != &rhs) {
11285  this->Reset();
11286  if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
11287  V8::CopyTracedGlobalReference(
11288  reinterpret_cast<const internal::Address* const*>(&rhs.val_),
11289  reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
11290  }
11291  }
11292  return *this;
11293 }

11299  this->Reset();
11300  if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
11301  this->SetSlotThreadSafe(
11302  this->New(isolate, other.val_, &this->val_,
11303  BasicTracedReference<T>::kWithoutDestructor));
11304 }

11350  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + I::kNodeClassIdOffset;
11351  *reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(addr) = class_id;
11352 }

11418  return;

11423 template<typename T>
11424 void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
11425  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Integer>::value, "type check");
11426  // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
11427  bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
11428  if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
11429  Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
11430  return;
11431  }
11432  Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
11433 }

11435 template<typename T>

11437  static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Boolean>::value, "type check");
11438  using I = internal::Internals;
11439  int root_index;
11440  if (value) {
11441  root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
11442  } else {
11443  root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
11444  }
11445  *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
11446 }

11697 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
11698 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11699  using A = internal::Address;
11700  using I = internal::Internals;
11701  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11702  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11703  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11704  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11705  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11706  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11707  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
11708  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11709  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(obj, offset);
11710 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11711  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11712  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11713  value = I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(obj, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11714 #endif
11715  internal::Isolate* isolate =
11716  internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj);
11717  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11718  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11719  }
11720 #endif
11721  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
11722 }
11723 
11724 
11725 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
11726 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11727  using A = internal::Address;
11728  using I = internal::Internals;
11729  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11730  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11731  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11732  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11733  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11734  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11735  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
11736  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11737 #ifdef V8_HEAP_SANDBOX
11738  offset += I::kEmbedderDataSlotRawPayloadOffset;
11739 #endif
11740  internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11741  A value = I::ReadExternalPointerField(
11742  isolate, obj, offset, internal::kEmbedderDataSlotPayloadTag);
11743  return reinterpret_cast<void*>(value);
11744  }
11745 #endif
11746  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
11747 }

11764 
11765 String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
11766  using A = internal::Address;
11767  using I = internal::Internals;
11768  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11769 
11770  ExternalStringResource* result;
11771  if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
11772  internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11773  A value =
11774  I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, obj, I::kStringResourceOffset,
11775  internal::kExternalStringResourceTag);
11776  result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
11777  } else {
11778  result = GetExternalStringResourceSlow();
11779  }
11780 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11781  VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
11782 #endif
11783  return result;
11784 }
11785 
11786 
11787 String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
11788  String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
11789  using A = internal::Address;
11790  using I = internal::Internals;
11791  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11792  int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
11793  *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
11794  ExternalStringResourceBase* resource;
11795  if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
11796  type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
11797  internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11798  A value =
11799  I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, obj, I::kStringResourceOffset,
11800  internal::kExternalStringResourceTag);
11801  resource = reinterpret_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
11802  } else {
11803  resource = GetExternalStringResourceBaseSlow(encoding_out);
11804  }
11805 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11806  VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
11807 #endif
11808  return resource;
11809 }

11820 bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
11821  using A = internal::Address;
11822  using I = internal::Internals;
11823  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11824  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11825  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11826  return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
11827 }

11838 bool Value::QuickIsNull() const {
11839  using A = internal::Address;
11840  using I = internal::Internals;
11841  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11842  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11843  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11844  return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kNullOddballKind);
11845 }

11850 #else
11851  return QuickIsNullOrUndefined();
11852 #endif
11853 }
11854 
11855 bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
11856  using A = internal::Address;
11857  using I = internal::Internals;
11858  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11859  if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11860  if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11861  int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
11862  return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
11863 }

12275  I::IntToSmi(I::kInferShouldThrowMode)) {

12341 
12342 Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
12343 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
12344  using A = internal::Address;
12345  using I = internal::Internals;
12346  A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
12347  A embedder_data =
12348  I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
12349  int value_offset =
12350  I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
12351  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(embedder_data, value_offset);
12352 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
12353  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
12354  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
12355  value =
12356  I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(embedder_data, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
12357 #endif
12358  internal::Isolate* isolate = internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(
12359  *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this));
12360  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
12361  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
12362 #else
12363  return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
12364 #endif
12365 }
12366 
12367 
12368 void* Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(int index) {
12369 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
12370  using A = internal::Address;
12371  using I = internal::Internals;
12372  A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
12373  A embedder_data =
12374  I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
12375  int value_offset =
12376  I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
12377 #ifdef V8_HEAP_SANDBOX
12378  value_offset += I::kEmbedderDataSlotRawPayloadOffset;
12379 #endif
12380  internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(ctx);
12381  return reinterpret_cast<void*>(
12382  I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, embedder_data, value_offset,
12383  internal::kEmbedderDataSlotPayloadTag));
12384 #else
12385  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index);
12386 #endif
12387 }

12392  if (data) internal::PerformCastCheck(data);
12393  return Local<T>(data);
